						<div class="postbody">Script, as in specification of mapper behavior in the config file? It wouldn't have to be at the gate level, more at a higher level, so that complex things like MMC3 could be mostly written in C internal to the emulator, and the script just specify how its registers are mapped, and any extra simple things. Something like that could be useful when one is wiring up their own cartridges in unique configurations, but still using standard components so that this could handle it. It obviously wouldn't handle something like Squeedo, though.</div>

